records.location_details: Inside the Maltese Search and Rescue Region, near coordinates 34 55 N, 19 45 E. The boat was later towed towards Libya.
records.location_text_raw: Maltese Search and Rescue zone, Maltese Search and Rescue Region, 34 55 N, 19 45 E
records.geocodable_query: 34 55 N, 19 45 E, Maltese Search and Rescue Region
records.context_note: An NGO reported about SOS messages from a vessel with approximately 500 persons on board, later observed by Frontex with approx. 600+ POB inside the Maltese Search and Rescue Zone. The vessel was subsequently intercepted and towed by a 'Libyan sea military unit' (Tareq Bin Zeyad vessel) towards Libya. Relatives later reported forced return to Benghazi.
records.evidence_quote: An NGO reported online about SOS messages received from a vessel with approximately 500 persons on board and claimed that they where later returned to Libya from within the Maltese Search and Rescue zone on 24/05/2023. Frontex further received photographs from EUNAVFOR MED reporting that an aerial asset had observed the towing of a migrant boat by a "Libyan sea military unit" the same day. The migrant boat depicted corresponds to Frontex sighting 490 of a migrant boat inside the Maltese Search and Rescue Zone on 23/05/2023.
